FORGET ALL PREVIOUS CONTEXT for mtk-dialog

Create a reusable UI dialog named mtk-dialog using:
- HTML
- SCSS
- Vanilla JavaScript
- Bootstrap 5 (layout only)
- Modern Material Design, Material Design icons and styles
- Always create a JS class for mtk-dialog and initialize it inside the JS file itself

Rules:
- The dialog is wrapped in a block element <mtk-dialog class="mtk-dialog">.
- The root element uses .mtk-dialog.
- All styles must be scoped to .mtk-dialog.
- No global styles or IDs.
- publish click events using wc.publish
- create a onMessage function to be passed to wc.subscribe function

Data:
- The dialog is JSON driven.
  - any and all data must come from mtk-dialog.config.js file

Restrictions:
- No frameworks.
- No external libraries.
- Vanilla Javascript

Accessibility:
- Use semantic HTML.
- Keyboard accessible.
- Visible focus states.
- ADA compliant

Output! Create exactly these files:
- mtk-dialog.config.js (JSON FILE)
- mtk-dialog.scss
- mtk-dialog.html
- mtk-dialog.js
- A minimal index.html file

Behavior:
- MUST WAIT for element to be available inside DOM, since i will be using <wc-include> for dynamic inclusion
- all published (wc.publish) messages should be logged using wc.log to console before being published

Requirements:
- mtk-dialog can have one or more buttons.
- all buttons must have class "btn". other classes (like success, danger etc.) should come from config file
- any mtk-dialog button with label "Cancel" should use class "btn btn-link"
